prompt: Create IOS XR 7.0.1 MDT config for incident response: stream IPv4 ACL telemetry statistics with higher cadence using ipv4-acl-oper sensor paths. Use gRPC no TLS. Server 192.0.2.187 port 57500. Sample every 30 seconds.
candidate:
telemetry model-driven
 sensor-group IPV4-ACL-STATS
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-ipv4-acl-oper:ipv4-acl-and-prefix-list
 !
 destination-group DG-GRPC
  address-family ipv4
   destination 192.0.2.187
    port 57500
    encoding self-describing-gpb
    protocol grpc no-tls
 !
 subscription SUB-IPV4-ACL
  sensor-group-id IPV4-ACL-STATS sample-interval 30000
  destination-group-id DG-GRPC
 !
expected:
telemetry model-driven
 sensor-group ACL-FAST
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-ipv4-acl-oper:ipv4-acl-and-prefix-list/access-list-manager/accesses/access/access-list-sequences/access-list-sequence
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-ipv4-acl-oper:ipv4-acl-and-prefix-list/prefix-list-manager/prefixes/prefix
 !
 subscription SUB-ACLF
  sensor-group-id ACL-FAST sample-interval 30000
  destination-group-id DG-ACLF
 !
 destination-group DG-ACLF
  address-family ipv4 192.0.2.187 port 57500
   encoding self-describing-gpb
   protocol grpc no-tls
  !
 !
!
rationale: The candidate config correctly uses the specified IP (192.0.2.187), port (57500), transport protocol (grpc no-tls), and encoding (self-describing-gpb). The sample interval is set to 30000 ms (30 seconds) as requested. However, the sensor-path in the candidate is less specific and does not include the detailed paths for ACL sequences and prefix lists as in the expectation, which are more aligned with the request for IPv4 ACL telemetry statistics. The sensor-group name and destination-group name differ but that is acceptable. Overall, the candidate meets the hard requirements but the sensor-paths are less precise and partially unrelated to the detailed expected paths.
